@card .primary
## `@card`
@divider

| parameter | description |
| --- | --- |
| type | block directive |
| path | `directives/builtins.js` |
| description | standard content container with a border and padding |
| `.left` | left-align content (default) |
| `.center` | center-align content |
| `.right` | right-align content |
| `.primary` | primary color variant |
| `.secondary` | secondary color variant |
| `.tertiary` | tertiary color variant |
| `.dark` | dark mode variant |
@row
@card .secondary
##* Usage

```mq
@card .dark
## Spooky
Join the dark side.
@end card

@card .center .tertiary
## Centered title
Content goes here.
@end card
```
@end card
@card .tertiary
##* Preview

@card .dark
##* Spooky
Join the dark side.
@end card

@card .center .tertiary
##* Centered title
Content goes here.
@end card

@end card
@end row
@end card
----
@card .primary
## `@dropdown`
@divider

| parameter | description |
| --- | --- |
| type | block directive |
| path | `directives/dropdown.js` |
| description | collapsible block that can be toggled open and closed. Starts in `closed` state by default. |
| `.open` `.expanded` `.default-open` | create the dropdown in the open state |
| `.disable-cache` | disables the caching behaviour |
| note | the `@dropdown` directive has built-in caching, and remembers its open/closed state |

@row
@card .secondary
##* Usage

```mq
@dropdown .open "Open by default"
You can see me!
@end dropdown
@dropdown "Closed by default"
And now you see me!
@end dropdown
@dropdown .open .disable-cache "Close me!"
Close me and refresh the page. I won't remember that you closed me. You can't get rid of me that easily!
@end dropdown
```
@end card
@card .tertiary
##* Preview

@dropdown .open "Open by default"
You can see me!
@end dropdown
@dropdown "Closed by default"
And now you see me!
@end dropdown
@dropdown .open .disable-cache "Close me!"
Close me and refresh the page. I won't remember that you closed me. You can't get rid of me >:)
@end dropdown
@end card
@end row
@end card

